            "fact_heading": "Facts",
            "fact_text": "Formation & OriginsThe primary difference between mined and lab grown diamonds is the way they are formed, and how and when they originate. Mined, or natural diamonds are formed deep within the Earth over millions and billions of years. These diamonds are formed due to extreme natural pressure and heat conditions. They are then brought to the surface via tectonic and volcanic activity. These diamonds are then extracted using large mining operations. While this natural formation makes mined diamonds a rare occurrence, due to a lack of control, a lot of natural factors and inconsistencies contribute to impurities, inclusions, and tints. On the other hand, lab grown diamonds are created under highly controlled technologically advanced labs using techniques that replicate the exact natural environmental conditions that occur during the formation of the natural diamond, only more controlled. This enables the lab grown diamonds to be produced in weeks instead of millions and billions of years like mined diamonds. Thus, the origin of the diamond goes a long way in impacting its rarity, quality, and accessibility. Whether you prioritize ethical sourcing, sustainability, affordability, quality, or innovation, understanding the formation and origin of the diamond you’re purchasing is essential to make an informed decision."
          }
        },
        "collection_block_7ACdbj": {
          "type": "collection_block",
          "settings": {
            "collection": "14kt-collection",
            "chips_text": "Necklace",
            "button_text": "View more design",
            "fact_heading": "Facts",
            "fact_text": "AccessibilityOne of the strongest advantages lab grown diamonds have over mined ones is that they’re quick and easy to produce, making them really affordable and accessible. Every mined diamond goes through an extensive process before it reaches your hands. The process includes exploration, extraction, labour-led mining, global transportation, and local distribution before it is finally certified. Every step involved contributes to the high prices which are ultimately paid by the end customer aka you. Even if you compare identical mined and lab grown diamonds, the mined stone will always be more expensive due to the aforementioned added costs. Lab grown diamonds skip quite a lot of expensive steps as they are created in controlled environments and you get to reap the benefits. These diamonds can be created quickly and efficiently, helping bring their costs down. The result? Lab grown diamonds on an average are at least 40 - 70 percent more affordable than mined natural diamonds while offering the same sparkle, brilliance and durability. For you, this means you get to pick a bigger, better gem, bringing your dream diamond within your reach. Indian Jewelry Buyers are price sensitive. We value practical and accessible luxury without compromising on the quality. Lab grown diamonds solve these issues perfectly through advancements in technology, streamlined distribution channels, and protection against global market fluctuations."
          }
